figgy.title: Some Numismatics::Reference objects can't be viewed or preserved
Figgy needs to be verified by Google
Set something up such that we run the preservation audit report again in X weeks or months

comments.body:
Proposal: Use our optional DLS discussion time every 4 months to ensemble kick off the preservation audit, and then the one two weeks after to review the results.

The next one would be May 9, review on May 23.

One after that is September 12, review on September 26

One after that is January 9, review on January 23. Review in January book the next three, or see if we can set it up as a recurring meeting.

The first problem resource I found was a PreservationObject pointing at a resource which is no longer set to preserve:

PO: ef
795a39-d750-4d91-93bb-c384d8923168
Resource: 22ce029e-571b-46be-9e97-83e50382b9d6 (https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/22ce029e-571b-46be-9e97-83e50382b9d6)

Since it's not set to preserve, PreservationObject.metadata_version doesn't get set when it re-preserves, then it runs the check and https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/jobs/cloud_fixity_job.rb#L71-L77 returns false.

I'm honestly not sure why it ever stops looping?

I have to go to a meeting, but recording this here:

I think if you ingest something as complete, the characterization process saves the FileSet without using the ChangeSetPersister, which means it doesn't update the preservation token.
